<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-033-708  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 033 708.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Jan 11 1990 n1340* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>US threatens Third World countries with duty on software exports.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   CSA Research Private Ltd. (cases).andO;Topic:     United States. Department of CommerceTariffComputer-Aided Software EngineeringGovernment FundingSingaporeSoftware PackagesInternational Trade.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>US THREATENS THIRD WORLD COUNTRIES WITHandM;DUTY ON SOFTWARE EXPORTSandM;In what could well become a cause celebre with third world countries led byHungary and India that have been investing heavily to build a software exportbusiness, the US Commerce Department has ruled that computer-aided softwareengineering programs from CSA Pte Ltd of Singapore were developed withgovernment finance and were therefore liable to import duties of 15.25% underun-fair trade rules if the preliminary finding is confirmed by a subsequentreview.andP;  The ruling was made in response to a petition by Visible SystemsCorp, Waltham, Massachusetts.andP;  As well as the likes of India and Hungary,Japanese and European companies could also well fall foul of the ruling.andO;</TEXT></DOC>